---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Manifesto" description="Manifesto for the fictional Commons Future Party.">
  <Section eyebrow="Manifesto" title="Freedom must become material, democratic, and durable." intro="A speculative public-facing manifesto for Freedom Commons Federalism.">
    <article class="max-w-none rounded-[2rem] border border-[#14233b]/10 bg-white/75 p-6 text-lg leading-8 text-[#334155] shadow-xl shadow-[#14233b]/8 sm:p-10">
      <p><strong class="text-[#14233b]">The Commons Future Party</strong> begins from a simple claim: freedom is not real when survival depends on submission. A person is not meaningfully free if a landlord, boss, border office, violent partner, monopoly platform, opaque algorithm, or distant bureaucracy can quietly narrow the life they are allowed to live.</p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-3xl font-black text-[#14233b]">Our horizon is abundance without domination.</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">Post-scarcity is not a slogan for pretending limits do not exist. It is a direction of travel: reduce scarcity sector by sector, beginning with the foundations of dignity. Build renewable energy, modular homes, automated farms, repair infrastructure, public compute, open manufacturing, medical capacity, and learning tools until money becomes less necessary for survival and creativity.</p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-3xl font-black text-[#14233b]">Our method is federation.</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">Local communities should remain real places with memory, care, and responsibility. They should not become prisons of birth, wealth, or conformity. Federation lets people belong locally and cooperate planetarily: sharing standards, rights, infrastructure, and mutual aid while preserving pluralism and peaceful exit.</p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-3xl font-black text-[#14233b]">Our technology is advisory, not sovereign.</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">Artificial intelligence can forecast, translate, simulate, coordinate logistics, audit corruption, expose hidden trade-offs, and help citizens understand policy. It must not rule. No person should lose rights, resources, movement, or dignity to an unappealable black box.</p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-3xl font-black text-[#14233b]">Our democracy delegates workload, never power.</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">Citizens should not have to become full-time policy analysts to retain control over their society. Delegates, assemblies, auditors, and AI tools can prepare proposals and explanations. Citizens keep approval, repeal, constitutional rights, and the final say.</p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-3xl font-black text-[#14233b]">Our justice seeks safety, repair, and return.</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">Serious harm may require secure restriction, but cruelty is not public safety. The aim is risk reduction, treatment, restitution, victim support, accountability, and reintegration wherever possible. Dignity is not a reward for perfect behaviour; it is a guardrail against domination.</p>
      <p class="mt-8 font-semibold text-[#14233b]">This is a fictional party, but the test is real: can we design institutions where shared power increases personal freedom, where technology serves people, and where no one is trapped by poverty, violence, borders, bosses, algorithms, or the state itself?</p>
    </article>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
